{"title_page": "James Stuart, 3rd Earl of Moray", "text_new": "'''James Stuart, 3rd Earl of Moray''' ([[1581 in Scotland|1581]]<ref>http://www.geni.com/people/James-Stuart/6000000004212455078</ref> &ndash; 6 August 1638) was the son of [[James Stewart, 2nd Earl of Moray]] and [[Elizabeth Stuart, 2nd Countess of Moray]].\n\nHe married Lady Anne Gordon, daughter of [[George Gordon, 1st Marquess of Huntly]] and [[Henrietta Stewart]], on 2 October 1607 (contract). He inherited the title [[Earl of Moray]] when his father was murdered by his future father-in-law in 1592. He was responsible for completing [[Castle Stuart]] on the banks of the [[Moray Firth]].<ref name=Castle>{{cite web|url=http://www.castlestuart.com/history.html|title=Castle Stuart - Our History|publisher=castlestuart.com|year=2010|accessdate=15 February 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091231051406/http://www.castlestuart.com/history.html|archivedate=31 December 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe died in 1638 and his title passed to his son, [[James Stuart, 4th Earl of Moray|James]]. His daughter Lady Henrietta Stuart married in 1662 Sir Hugh Campbell of Cawdor, elder (? - 11 March 1716), [[Knight]]ed in 1660, and had issue.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* http://www.thepeerage.com/p271.htm#i2702\n* Charles Mosley, editor, Burke's Peerage, Baronetage & Knightage, 107th edition, 3 volumes (Wilmington, Delaware, U.S.A.: Burke's Peerage (Genealogical Books) Ltd, 2003).\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-reg|sct}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Earl of Moray]] | before=[[James Stewart, 2nd Earl of Moray|James Stuart]] | after=[[James Stuart, 4th Earl of Moray|James Stuart]] | years=}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moray, James Stuart, 3rd Earl Of}}\n[[Category:1638 deaths]]\n[[Category:Earls of Moray]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n[[Category:16th-century Scottish peers]]\n[[Category:17th-century Scottish peers]]\n[[Category:Members of the Convention of the Estates of Scotland 1630]]\n\n\n{{Scotland-earl-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''James Stuart, 3rd Earl of Moray''' ([[1581 in Scotland|1581]]<ref>http://www.geni.com/people/James-Stuart/6000000004212455078</ref> &ndash; 6 August 1638) was the son of [[James Stewart, 2nd Earl of Moray]] and [[Elizabeth Stuart, 2nd Countess of Moray]].\n\nHe married Lady Anne Gordon, daughter of [[George Gordon, 1st Marquess of Huntly]] and Lady Henrietta Stuart, on 2 October 1607 (contract). He inherited the title '''Earl of Moray''' when his father was murdered by his future father-in-law in 1592. He was responsible for completing [[Castle Stuart]] on the banks of the [[Moray Firth]].<ref name=Castle>{{cite web|url=http://www.castlestuart.com/history.html|title=Castle Stuart - Our History|publisher=castlestuart.com|year=2010|accessdate=15 February 2010|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091231051406/http://www.castlestuart.com/history.html|archivedate=31 December 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe died in 1638 and his title passed to his son, [[James Stuart, 4th Earl of Moray|James]]. His daughter Lady Henrietta Stuart married in 1662 Sir Hugh Campbell of Cawdor, elder (? - 11 March 1716), [[Knight]]ed in 1660, and had issue.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n* http://www.thepeerage.com/p271.htm#i2702\n* Charles Mosley, editor, Burke's Peerage, Baronetage & Knightage, 107th edition, 3 volumes (Wilmington, Delaware, U.S.A.: Burke's Peerage (Genealogical Books) Ltd, 2003).\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-reg|sct}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Earl of Moray]] | before=[[James Stewart, 2nd Earl of Moray|James Stuart]] | after=[[James Stuart, 4th Earl of Moray|James Stuart]] | years=}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Moray, James Stuart, 3rd Earl Of}}\n[[Category:1638 deaths]]\n[[Category:Earls of Moray]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n[[Category:16th-century Scottish peers]]\n[[Category:17th-century Scottish peers]]\n[[Category:Members of the C