 {{small|(\u05d4\u05e9\u05e7\u05d8 \u05e9\u05e0\u05e9\u05d0\u05e8)}}\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|154\t\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|158\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2006}}\n|[[Eddie Butler (singer)|Eddie Butler]]\n|English, Hebrew\n|\"[[Together We Are One (song)|Together We Are One]]\" \n|align=center|23\n|align=center|4\n|colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"-9999\" {{N/A|Top 11 previous year}}{{efn|name=note2|According to the [[Rules of the Eurovision Song Contest|then-Eurovision rules]], the top ten non-[[Eurovision Song Contest#Big Four and Big Five|Big Four]] countries from the previous year along with the Big Four automatically qualified for the Grand Final without having to compete in semi-finals. For example, if Germany and France placed inside the top ten, the 11th and 12th spots were advanced to next year's Grand Final along with all countries ranked in the top ten.}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2007}}\n|[[Teapacks]]\n|English, [[French language|French]], Hebrew\n|\"[[Push the Button (Teapacks song)|Push the Button]]\" \n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|24\n|align=center|17\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2008}}\n|[[Bo'az Ma'uda]]\n|Hebrew, English\n|\"[[The Fire In Your Eyes]]\" \n|align=center|9\n|align=center|124\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|104\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2009}}\n|[[Achinoam Nini|Noa]] & [[Mira Awad]]\n|English, Hebrew, [[Arabic language|Arabic]]\n|\"[[There Must Be Another Way]]\" \n|align=center|16\n|align=center|53\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|75\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2010}}\n|[[Harel Skaat]]\n|Hebrew\n|\"[[Milim]]\" {{small|(\u05de\u05d9\u05dc\u05d9\u05dd)}}\n|align=center|14\n|align=center|71\n|align=center|8\n|align=center|71\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2011}}\n|Dana International\n|Hebrew, English\n|\"[[Ding Dong (Dana International song)|Ding Dong]]\" {{small|(\u05d3\u05d9\u05e0\u05d2 \u05d3\u05d5\u05e0\u05d2)}}\n|colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|15\n|align=center|38\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2012}}\n|[[Izabo]]\n|English, Hebrew\n|\"[[Time (Izabo song)|Time]]\" \n|align=center|13\n|align=center|33\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2013}}\n|[[Moran Mazor]]\n|Hebrew\n|\"[[Rak Bishvilo]]\" {{small|(\u05e8\u05e7 \u05d1\u05e9\u05d1\u05d9\u05dc\u05d5)}}\n|align=center|14\n|align=center|40\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2014}}\n|[[Mei Finegold]]\n|English, Hebrew\n|\"[[Same Heart]]\" \n|align=center|14\n|align=center|19 \n|-\n!{{Escyr|2015}}\n|[[Nadav Guedj]]\n|English\n|\"[[Golden Boy (Nadav Guedj song)|Golden Boy]]\"\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|97\n|style=\"background:#c96;\" align=center|3\n|style=\"background:#c96;\" align=center|151\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2016}}\n|[[Hovi Star]]\n|English\n|\"[[Made of Stars]]\"\n|align=center|14\n|align=center|135\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|147\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2017}}\n|[[Imri Ziv|IMRI]] \n|English\n|\"[[I Feel Alive]]\"\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|39\n|style=\"background:#c96;\" align=center|3\n|style=\"background:#c96;\" align=center|207\n|-style=\"background:gold;\"\n!{{Escyr|2018}}\n|[[Netta Barzilai|Netta]] \n|English{{efn| Contains several words in Hebrew.}}\n|\"[[Toy (song)|Toy]]\"\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|529\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|283\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2019}}\n|[[Kobi Marimi]]\n|English\n|\"[[Home (Kobi Marimi song)|Home]]\"\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|35\n|colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"-9999\" {{N/A|Host country}}{{efn|name=note3|The host country did not have to compete in the semi-finals.}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#A4EAA9\"\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2020}}}}\n|[[Eden Alene]]\n| English, [[Amharic]]{{Efn|Contains phrases in Hebrew and Arabic.}}\n| \"[[Feker Libi]]\" {{small|(\u134d\u1245\u122d \u120d\u1264)}}\n|colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Contest cancelled}}{{Efn|The 2020 contest was cancelled due to<br>the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].}} '''X'''\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2021}}\n| Eden Alene<ref>{{cite web |url=https://eurovisionworld.com/esc/eden-alena-back-for-eurovision-2021 |title=Eden Alena back for Eurovision 2021 |first=Steven |last=Spiteri |date=22 March 2020 |website=Eurovisionworld}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|