6;\" align=center|207\n|-style=\"background:gold;\"\n!{{Escyr|2018}}\n|[[Netta Barzilai|Netta]] \n|English{{efn| Contains several words in Hebrew.}}\n|\"[[Toy (song)|Toy]]\"\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|529\n|align=center|1\n|align=center|283\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2019}}\n|[[Kobi Marimi]]\n|English\n|\"[[Home (Kobi Marimi song)|Home]]\"\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|35\n|colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"-9999\" {{N/A|Host country}}{{efn|name=note3|The host country did not have to compete in the semi-finals.}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#A4EAA9\"\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2020}}}}{{Efn|The 2020 contest was cancelled due to<br>the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].}}\n|[[Eden Alene]]\n| English, [[Amharic]]{{Efn|Contains phrases in Hebrew and Arabic.}}\n| \"[[Feker Libi]]\" {{small|(\u134d\u1245\u122d \u120d\u1264)}}\n|colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Contest Cancelled}} '''X'''\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2021}}\n| Eden Alene<ref>{{cite web |url=https://eurovisionworld.com/esc/eden-alena-back-for-eurovision-2021 |title=Eden Alena back for Eurovision 2021 |first=Steven |last=Spiteri |date=22 March 2020 |website=Eurovisionworld}}</ref>\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n===Congratulations: 50 Years of the Eurovision Song Contest===\n{{further|Congratulations: 50 Years of the Eurovision Song Contest}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Artist\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Language\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Title\n!colspan=\"4\"|At Congratulations\n!colspan=\"3\"|At Eurovision\n|-\n!style=\"width:50px;\"|Final\n!style=\"width:50px;\"|Points \n!style=\"width:50px;\"|Semi\n!style=\"width:50px;\"|Points\n!style=\"width:50px;\"|Year\n!style=\"width:50px;\"|Place\n!style=\"width:50px;\"|Points\n|- \n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Dana International]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|[[Hebrew language|Hebrew]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|\"[[Diva (Dana International song)|Diva]]\" {{small|(\u05d3\u05d9\u05d5\u05d5\u05d4)}}\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|13\n|39\n|bgcolor=\"gold\"|{{Escyr|1998}}\n|bgcolo